DAVID MILLAR v. AGNES L. MILLAR. Decided March 10th, 1926.

The cause was argued before Bond, C. J., Pattison, Ubneb, Adkins, Oefdtt, Digges, and Pabke, JJ.

Charles W. Heuisler, with whom was Morrill N. Packard on the brief, for the appellant. Watson E. Sherwood, for the appellee. Urner, J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court, affirming the decree, with costs.
